cs.OS, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PF 

The paper deals with the problem of non-uniform memory access (NUMA) in multi-socket machines, which is a common issue in operating systems (cs.OS) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The proposed solution involves replication and migration of page-tables, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and system-level optimization (cs.SY). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed solution involves performance analysis (cs.PF).
